Founders of The Peace Train project which formed South Africa’s first multiracial choir in 1993, Sharon Katz and Nonhlanhla Wanda will feature their new album, Side by Side when they perform during this week’s Soul Sunday Sessions at 1:30pm at Northwood Crusaders Sports Club on 25 February. The line-up also includes singer-songwriter Jessica Martins and percussionist Nishalin Pillay. Entrance is free.